{"build_type":"library","description":"Rename one package fully, given old name, new name, and roots. Re-enumerates the universe from disk each call (so it is safe to call in a loop while earlier renames have already moved files). Finds the old package's single function key; renames that symbol + every call site across all packages via ed_all_packages (g_rename_match/g_rename_to); rewrites package_name+module_name; renames the directory and the .ipm file (rename syscall 82). The reusable core behind both the single rename-package tool and the batch rename-packages-from-map tool. Reuses enumerate_universe_packages, count_members_inside_container_value, begin_empty_sequence_document_value, collect_universe_paths_into_array, find_package_doc_by_package_name, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, encode_boolean_payload_document_value, attach_named_member_inside_mapping, ed_all_packages, fetch_member_residing_within_sequence, build_store_path, create_empty_string_buffer, append_cstring_into_string_buffer, rewrite_package_name_fields_in_file.","module_name":"rename-single-package-through-identifier","package_name":"rename-single-package-through-identifier","module_globals":[{"global_name":"g_rename_match","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_rename_to","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"rename-single-package-through-identifier":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"old","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"new","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"roots","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fd","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function_definitions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_